$$
N = 40
$$

#### Find Q1

$$
Q_1 = \frac{N}{4} = 10
$$

10 lies in class **19.5–29.5**

$$
Q_1 = 19.5 + \left(\frac{10 - 3}{7}\right)\times 10
$$

$$
Q_1 = 19.5 + 10 = 29.5
$$

#### Find Q3

$$
Q_3 = \frac{3N}{4} = 30
$$

30 lies in class **39.5–49.5**

$$
Q_3 = 39.5 + \left(\frac{30 - 22}{10}\right)\times 10
$$

$$
Q_3 = 39.5 + 8 = 47.5
$$


#### Quartile Deviation

$$
QD = \frac{47.5 - 29.5}{2} = 9
$$

$$
\text{Coeff. QD} = \frac{47.5 - 29.5}{47.5 + 29.5} = 0.234
$$
